      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the whistling is loud and persistent, waiting an hour on just an antihistamine might not be enough, even if it is just hay fever. While antihistamines help with allergy symptoms, they don't always address acute airway constriction. If you are worried, take the pill, but also try to breathe deeply through your nose and keep moving to get some fresh air while staying calm. If you feel any shortness of breath that doesn't improve, you should get checked out.",
