      "content": "If you are struggling to take a full breath, you should not be \"just waiting it out\"—that is a sign you need immediate medical attention. Lying down in the shade is fine for comfort, but if your breathing is compromised, you need to sit upright to help your lungs expand fully. Since you are concerned about your breathing, take your allergy pill, but also consider a quick, non-emergency trip to urgent care just to be sure.",
